1
00:00:02,910 --> 00:00:04,800
The anti-nausea IV is done,

2
00:00:04,800 --> 00:00:07,740
so we'll start the chemotherapy now.

3
00:00:07,740 --> 00:00:10,075
Now's when the real fight begins.

4
00:00:10,075 --> 00:00:12,275
The side effects will be tough.

5
00:00:16,840 --> 00:00:20,480
Her stamina and appetite
have dropped so suddenly.

6
00:00:21,986 --> 00:00:25,156
We might see the treatment
working around next week.

7
00:00:26,230 --> 00:00:27,320
Koharu?

8
00:00:29,090 --> 00:00:30,710
Maybe I'll cut...

9
00:00:32,530 --> 00:00:33,940
my hair...

10
00:00:38,150 --> 00:00:39,550
Hey, Kakeru!

11
00:00:42,335 --> 00:00:43,780
Hello?

12
00:00:43,780 --> 00:00:45,160
Kakeru?

13
00:00:47,225 --> 00:00:49,040
Oh, what's up?

14
00:00:49,040 --> 00:00:51,345
- What's wrong?
- You okay?

15
00:00:52,155 --> 00:00:53,390
Yeah.

16
00:00:53,390 --> 00:00:56,425
Since you're down,
I have amazing news for you.

17
00:00:56,425 --> 00:00:58,395
The king of good news!

18
00:00:59,360 --> 00:01:01,490
Ta-da!

19
00:01:04,345 --> 00:01:05,700
Fireworks...

20
00:01:05,700 --> 00:01:08,760
It's on New Year's,
since summer didn't happen.

21
00:01:08,760 --> 00:01:10,920
And it's one train station away.

22
00:01:10,920 --> 00:01:13,360
It's a miracle, isn't it?

23
00:01:13,360 --> 00:01:16,000
And I'm the genius who found it.

24
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:19,170
We were thinking
we could help out somehow too.

25
00:01:19,170 --> 00:01:21,525
Well, it's still a while from now.

26
00:01:21,525 --> 00:01:23,445
We can fulfill her wish...

27
00:01:24,665 --> 00:01:27,370
Maybe we shouldn't.

28
00:01:27,370 --> 00:01:28,370
Huh?

29
00:01:32,520 --> 00:01:33,580
Kakeru?

30
00:01:35,335 --> 00:01:38,190
Koharu might not want to remember.

31
00:01:38,190 --> 00:01:40,020
No, there's no way.

32
00:01:42,350 --> 00:01:43,790
How would you know?

33
00:01:48,070 --> 00:01:51,080
Is there even a way to help her?

34
00:01:55,180 --> 00:01:57,070
Sorry, I gotta go.

35
00:02:00,595 --> 00:02:03,110
Are you really sure about this?

36
00:02:03,110 --> 00:02:04,110
Yeah.

37
00:02:05,116 --> 00:02:08,656
You could keep it for yourself, you know?

38
00:02:09,410 --> 00:02:10,600
It's fine.

39
00:02:11,740 --> 00:02:14,140
<i>I want to give it to the children.</i>

40
00:02:21,300 --> 00:02:22,700
Here we go...

41
00:02:46,730 --> 00:02:48,010
Mom.

42
00:02:50,330 --> 00:02:51,780
Just a moment.

43
00:03:03,940 --> 00:03:06,730
That's strange. What's gotten into me?

44
00:03:12,110 --> 00:03:13,330
Sorry.

45
00:03:14,550 --> 00:03:16,170
Let's do it another time.

46
00:03:17,480 --> 00:03:18,480
Okay?

47
00:03:21,480 --> 00:03:22,810
Let's take these off.

48
00:04:05,245 --> 00:04:10,292
This subject re-examines
the norms of modern society.

49
00:04:10,292 --> 00:04:13,712
As researchers also make discoveries
about their own cultures.

50
00:04:15,215 --> 00:04:17,180
In fact, cultural anthropology

51
00:04:17,180 --> 00:04:20,590
was originally systematized
by Bronisław Malinowski,

52
00:04:20,590 --> 00:04:24,450
a Polish-born British
cultural anthropologist.

53
00:04:24,450 --> 00:04:26,035
He established fieldwork...

54
00:04:26,035 --> 00:04:28,305
Excuse me, is this seat taken?

55
00:04:29,630 --> 00:04:30,950
No.

56
00:04:32,110 --> 00:04:38,130
In the cultural anthropology fieldwork,
the research target's place of origin...

57
00:04:52,900 --> 00:04:54,010
Excuse me.

58
00:04:55,205 --> 00:04:57,080
Koharu's mother.

59
00:04:57,080 --> 00:04:58,720
Kakeru.

60
00:05:04,660 --> 00:05:08,680
The campus is more relaxed than I expected.

61
00:05:10,811 --> 00:05:15,961
I mean, parents usually only come
for open campus days or school festivals.

62
00:05:15,961 --> 00:05:18,491
They only get to see special events.

63
00:05:20,580 --> 00:05:22,120
That's true.

64
00:05:23,370 --> 00:05:25,450
I should have visited more often.

65
00:05:26,780 --> 00:05:30,480
But then again, I can come anytime, right?

66
00:05:37,045 --> 00:05:38,745
Koharu told me...

67
00:05:40,430 --> 00:05:42,660
about her illness.

68
00:05:47,970 --> 00:05:49,995
Is it true?

69
00:05:49,995 --> 00:05:52,515
What did that girl say?

70
00:05:58,830 --> 00:06:00,920
That she has six months left.

71
00:06:02,900 --> 00:06:04,470
I see...

72
00:06:05,855 --> 00:06:09,200
If she lasts six months,
it would be a blessing.

73
00:06:09,200 --> 00:06:11,460
She hasn't been doing well lately.

74
00:06:14,355 --> 00:06:19,260
I'm sorry. I'm already causing you
so much pain.

75
00:06:21,220 --> 00:06:24,120
It must be even harder for you.

76
00:06:24,850 --> 00:06:28,480
Yeah. It's tough.

77
00:06:32,860 --> 00:06:38,520
I wonder why I couldn't make her stronger,
more resilient when I gave birth.

78
00:06:45,565 --> 00:06:47,190
Thank you for coming today.

79
00:06:47,190 --> 00:06:49,990
No, I didn't do anything.

80
00:06:49,990 --> 00:06:54,265
I actually came today
to withdraw her from college.

81
00:06:54,265 --> 00:06:56,145
Koharu asked me to.

82
00:06:56,980 --> 00:06:57,980
What?

83
00:06:58,660 --> 00:07:03,590
But I couldn't accept it,
so I changed it to a leave of absence.

84
00:07:03,590 --> 00:07:06,355
Though she might not come back.

85
00:07:06,355 --> 00:07:07,795
She's strong.

86
00:07:11,580 --> 00:07:13,040
Koharu...

87
00:07:14,207 --> 00:07:16,777
is stronger than anyone I've ever met.

88
00:07:21,570 --> 00:07:23,110
If it were me,

89
00:07:24,090 --> 00:07:26,090
I couldn't smile like that.

90
00:07:27,470 --> 00:07:29,400
She's lived with this illness.

91
00:07:34,130 --> 00:07:36,440
But she doesn't tell anyone.

92
00:07:37,580 --> 00:07:39,450
She doesn't make excuses.

93
00:07:41,790 --> 00:07:43,980
She lives to the fullest.

94
00:07:46,750 --> 00:07:49,100
Meeting up in this square,

95
00:07:50,210 --> 00:07:52,090
attending classes together,

96
00:07:53,016 --> 00:07:55,126
chatting on the way home...

97
00:07:58,800 --> 00:08:01,090
I took it all for granted.

98
00:08:13,490 --> 00:08:15,730
I should have told her...

99
00:08:17,810 --> 00:08:19,910
that she's amazing.

100
00:08:21,800 --> 00:08:23,500
That she's admirable.

101
00:08:29,770 --> 00:08:31,140
Thank you...

102
00:08:33,200 --> 00:08:35,000
for being in Koharu's life.

103
00:08:42,360 --> 00:08:43,770
The bookmark...

104
00:08:45,920 --> 00:08:46,960
Um...

105
00:08:49,988 --> 00:08:53,573
That yellow bookmark... Where is it now?

106
00:08:56,940 --> 00:08:58,290
No way...

107
00:09:00,990 --> 00:09:02,540
Koharu is...

108
00:09:04,810 --> 00:09:08,740
I don't want to believe it either.

109
00:09:08,740 --> 00:09:11,210
Kakeru sure is something else.

110
00:09:11,880 --> 00:09:14,510
How could he bear this on his own?

111
00:09:16,810 --> 00:09:18,820
He's that kind of guy, huh?

112
00:09:27,996 --> 00:09:30,606
Regarding the next round of chemotherapy...

113
00:09:34,190 --> 00:09:35,560
Koharu?

114
00:09:37,995 --> 00:09:39,125
Can I just...

115
00:09:40,960 --> 00:09:42,910
stop the treatment?

116
00:09:47,765 --> 00:09:51,000
Shall we take a short break?

117
00:09:52,680 --> 00:09:54,670
Not a break.

118
00:09:56,040 --> 00:09:57,160
Just...

119
00:10:03,390 --> 00:10:04,640
That's fine.

120
00:10:07,465 --> 00:10:12,446
A doctor cannot proceed with treatment
against a patient's wishes.

121
00:10:16,408 --> 00:10:21,290
Besides, you've already
begun preparing for the end.

122
00:10:21,290 --> 00:10:23,480
With that mindset, treatment is...

123
00:10:25,550 --> 00:10:27,440
I'm not preparing for that.

124
00:10:28,730 --> 00:10:30,510
Yes, you are.

125
00:10:31,810 --> 00:10:33,240
Mentally preparing.

126
00:10:41,485 --> 00:10:43,874
- Come in.
- Thank you.

127
00:10:48,770 --> 00:10:50,130
Here.

128
00:10:52,095 --> 00:10:53,660
Wait here.

129
00:11:07,420 --> 00:11:08,870
Koharu's room.

130
00:11:10,980 --> 00:11:12,540
It's lonely, isn't it?

131
00:11:13,480 --> 00:11:18,400
The day before she was hospitalized,
she wanted to clean it out.

132
00:11:19,720 --> 00:11:22,130
It's like she's not expecting to return.

133
00:11:24,770 --> 00:11:27,290
This is what you wanted, right?

134
00:11:28,340 --> 00:11:29,820
This is it.

135
00:11:30,680 --> 00:11:32,320
It was in the trash.

136
00:11:34,015 --> 00:11:37,960
That girl's really something else.

137
00:11:40,140 --> 00:11:41,610
I'll make some tea.

138
00:11:46,185 --> 00:11:47,990
Four years ago,

139
00:11:47,990 --> 00:11:52,375
you developed intraocular lymphoma
and lost your sight.

140
00:11:53,365 --> 00:11:56,640
But you never gave up on living.

141
00:11:56,640 --> 00:12:00,105
You learned braille,
and even went to college.

142
00:12:06,030 --> 00:12:08,100
Are you really sure?

143
00:12:08,979 --> 00:12:13,708
Letting go of everything you worked
so desperately to obtain...

144
00:12:13,708 --> 00:12:16,470
and giving up...

145
00:12:16,470 --> 00:12:18,100
I don't want to.

146
00:12:20,350 --> 00:12:24,230
It's not like I'm letting go
because I want to.

147
00:12:25,340 --> 00:12:27,400
But if I cling on...

148
00:12:28,905 --> 00:12:33,110
all I'll do is cause pain
to everyone around me.

149
00:12:33,110 --> 00:12:35,100
I'll just be a burden.

150
00:12:42,920 --> 00:12:46,620
If I don't let go,
knowing it'll hurt the people I love,

151
00:12:48,090 --> 00:12:50,070
I'm being too selfish.

152
00:12:51,670 --> 00:12:54,570
It's not up to you if they feel hurt or not.

153
00:12:56,330 --> 00:13:00,760
<i>That's up to the people you love to decide.</i>

154
00:13:12,160 --> 00:13:13,390
What's left?

155
00:13:15,946 --> 00:13:18,166
On your bookmark list.

156
00:13:19,250 --> 00:13:20,820
Ah...

157
00:13:21,586 --> 00:13:23,546
It's still a secret.

158
00:13:24,310 --> 00:13:30,370
<i>But there are lots of things I want to try
that I haven't experienced yet.</i>

159
00:13:56,156 --> 00:13:57,266
Yuuko!

160
00:13:58,090 --> 00:14:00,640
Thanks, this really helps.

161
00:14:01,390 --> 00:14:02,390
Bye.

162
00:14:03,230 --> 00:14:04,460
Wait!

163
00:14:09,160 --> 00:14:10,260
I heard...

164
00:14:12,010 --> 00:14:13,470
about Koharu.

165
00:14:15,356 --> 00:14:16,576
I just...

166
00:14:17,965 --> 00:14:20,210
don't know what to do anymore.

167
00:14:20,210 --> 00:14:22,120
I don't really know either.

168
00:14:23,822 --> 00:14:26,852
But I have to go.

169
00:14:28,075 --> 00:14:29,790
What about you?

170
00:14:29,790 --> 00:14:30,880
Huh?

171
00:14:31,895 --> 00:14:35,680
Are you okay, Kakeru?

172
00:14:35,680 --> 00:14:38,135
- I'm fine.
- No, you're not.

173
00:14:39,305 --> 00:14:41,740
- I mean...
- You're not okay.

174
00:14:43,550 --> 00:14:44,670
Yuuko.

175
00:14:46,190 --> 00:14:47,480
I mean...

176
00:14:53,226 --> 00:14:54,816
She's dying.

177
00:14:59,160 --> 00:15:01,190
No, sorry...

178
00:15:06,776 --> 00:15:11,736
It's just, if you end up suffering alone
as you did with Haruto...

179
00:15:20,650 --> 00:15:22,390
Thanks to Koharu...

180
00:15:25,936 --> 00:15:27,956
no matter what happens...

181
00:15:29,137 --> 00:15:34,030
I can still try to move forward like this.

182
00:15:38,810 --> 00:15:40,430
Sorry for worrying you.

183
00:15:48,320 --> 00:15:50,820
A list of things I want to do in my life.

184
00:15:52,060 --> 00:15:54,490
"Make friends."

185
00:15:56,510 --> 00:15:58,410
<i>"Go to a drinking party."</i>

186
00:16:02,090 --> 00:16:03,770
<i>"Play the piano."</i>

187
00:16:07,160 --> 00:16:09,400
<i>"Set off fireworks."</i>

188
00:16:14,040 --> 00:16:15,420
<i>Fall in love.</i>

189
00:16:41,420 --> 00:16:42,690
Mom?

190
00:16:44,686 --> 00:16:46,216
It's Kakeru.

191
00:16:48,860 --> 00:16:50,470
Please leave.

192
00:16:52,550 --> 00:16:53,770
Let's go see...

193
00:16:55,037 --> 00:16:56,347
fireworks.

194
00:16:58,130 --> 00:16:59,200
Huh?

195
00:17:02,665 --> 00:17:04,980
Have you forgotten what I said?

196
00:17:04,980 --> 00:17:06,600
I remember.

197
00:17:06,600 --> 00:17:10,225
Then please, don't get involved anymore.

198
00:17:10,225 --> 00:17:11,855
But Koharu...

199
00:17:15,455 --> 00:17:19,050
You remember, don't you? All of it.

200
00:17:21,100 --> 00:17:22,740
What do you mean?

201
00:17:24,086 --> 00:17:26,531
There are fireworks on New Year's.

202
00:17:26,531 --> 00:17:28,571
And it's pretty close by.

203
00:17:29,890 --> 00:17:33,400
Ushio said it's a miracle
they're doing it in winter.

204
00:17:34,800 --> 00:17:36,340
After New Year's...

205
00:17:37,796 --> 00:17:39,126
Yeah.

206
00:17:42,340 --> 00:17:44,350
Can't you see?

207
00:17:45,760 --> 00:17:48,340
My body is falling apart right now.

208
00:17:49,900 --> 00:17:52,090
I can't eat anything.

209
00:17:53,097 --> 00:17:55,257
I can barely even get up.

210
00:17:57,700 --> 00:18:01,820
And my hair will start falling out soon.

211
00:18:05,397 --> 00:18:06,747
But...

212
00:18:10,390 --> 00:18:12,370
I can't see.

213
00:18:17,639 --> 00:18:19,999
I can only rely on my touch...

214
00:18:21,180 --> 00:18:23,810
to imagine how horrible I look.

215
00:18:27,990 --> 00:18:29,440
I'm most likely...

216
00:18:30,870 --> 00:18:32,240
going to die...

217
00:18:33,840 --> 00:18:35,340
next year.

218
00:18:38,410 --> 00:18:39,890
Let's keep fighting.

219
00:18:44,855 --> 00:18:45,950
And together, we'll...

220
00:18:45,950 --> 00:18:47,970
Why would you say that?

221
00:18:51,110 --> 00:18:55,170
Do you know how cruel those words are?

222
00:18:57,520 --> 00:18:58,520
Yeah.

223
00:19:00,540 --> 00:19:02,900
- Then why...
- Since you're not done.

224
00:19:24,690 --> 00:19:26,790
The list of things you want to do.

225
00:19:29,050 --> 00:19:30,730
It's not done yet.

226
00:19:37,140 --> 00:19:38,870
You told me.

227
00:19:39,970 --> 00:19:44,010
Even with higher hurdles,
it doesn't mean you can't jump them.

228
00:19:49,582 --> 00:19:54,932
In fact, it feels amazing
when you manage to jump over them.

229
00:20:07,640 --> 00:20:09,510
I know you can do it.

230
00:20:14,800 --> 00:20:16,790
I'm sure of it.

231
00:20:25,900 --> 00:20:27,340
I...

232
00:20:31,720 --> 00:20:33,250
I...

233
00:20:34,610 --> 00:20:36,570
want to see the fireworks too.

234
00:20:42,040 --> 00:20:43,750
Then stay alive.

235
00:20:51,407 --> 00:20:52,857
First, let's...

236
00:20:54,276 --> 00:20:55,816
get to the new year.

237
00:20:59,250 --> 00:21:01,490
And when we see the fireworks,

238
00:21:04,817 --> 00:21:07,337
we'll set our next goal together.

239
00:21:17,740 --> 00:21:19,750
Just like that, forever,

240
00:21:22,660 --> 00:21:24,250
let's fight together.

241
00:21:40,500 --> 00:21:42,280
It's unfair.

242
00:21:47,130 --> 00:21:48,150
I'm sorry.

243
00:21:50,894 --> 00:21:56,140
Do you know how hard it was
for me to push you away?

244
00:22:03,660 --> 00:22:04,720
I'm sorry.

245
00:22:13,840 --> 00:22:15,270
I'm...

246
00:22:18,890 --> 00:22:20,910
a bad loser, you know.

247
00:22:26,780 --> 00:22:27,780
Okay.

248
00:22:30,340 --> 00:22:34,510
It'll be too late to back out later.

249
00:22:37,896 --> 00:22:39,286
Understood.

250
00:22:41,705 --> 00:22:45,460
Why are you smiling? I'm being serious here.

251
00:22:48,190 --> 00:22:49,650
I'm not smiling.

252
00:23:06,600 --> 00:23:07,730
See?

253
00:23:10,820 --> 00:23:12,180
Liar.

254
00:23:16,140 --> 00:23:17,540
Back at you.

255
00:23:24,628 --> 00:23:26,090
I won't die...

256
00:23:28,890 --> 00:23:31,330
until we see the fireworks together.

257
00:23:36,520 --> 00:23:37,520
Yeah.

258
00:23:45,345 --> 00:23:48,710
Koharu's body was so light.

259
00:23:48,710 --> 00:23:50,640
You'll go to the fireworks, right?

260
00:23:50,640 --> 00:23:53,515
Yeah. I'll be better by then.

261
00:23:53,515 --> 00:23:57,960
Koharu might not get better,
even with effort.

262
00:23:57,960 --> 00:23:59,960
I really don't want to die.
